Author: Uladzislau Rezki (Sony) <urezki@gmail.com>

mm/vmalloc: Use dedicated unbound workqueue for vmap purge/drain

This commit switches drain_vmap_area_work to use a dedicated WQ_UNBOUND
workqueue to allow the scheduler to run the background task on any
available CPU. It also uses WQ_MEM_RECLAIM to ensure forward progress
under memory pressure and simplifies purge helper scheduling.

Cc: lirongqing <lirongqing@baidu.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/all/20260319074307.2325-1-lirongqing@baidu.com/

